================================================================================
1. Original Code
================================================================================

All source code in this repository (libcloner/, cli/, dfu-remote/, android/,
tests/, scripts/) was written independently by the thingino project contributors.
No source code was copied from Ingenic's proprietary cloner tool or any other
proprietary software.

================================================================================
2. USB Protocol
================================================================================

The Ingenic USB boot protocol used by this tool was determined through clean-room
reverse engineering of USB traffic between Ingenic devices and the vendor tool,
using standard USB analysis tools (Wireshark, USBPcap). This was done for the
purpose of hardware interoperability, which is permitted under:

  - U.S. Copyright Act §117 and DMCA §1201(f) (interoperability exception)
  - EU Software Directive 2009/24/EC, Article 6 (decompilation for interoperability)

The USB vendor request codes (0x00-0x26) and bulk transfer protocol are
functional interfaces required to communicate with Ingenic SoC hardware.
Functional interfaces are not copyrightable (Lotus v. Borland, Oracle v. Google).

================================================================================
3. Firmware Binaries (firmware/cloner/)
================================================================================

The SPL (Secondary Program Loader) and U-Boot binaries in the firmware/cloner/
directory are compiled from Ingenic's fork of Das U-Boot, which is licensed
under the GNU General Public License version 2 (GPL-2.0). These binaries are
redistributed under the terms of GPL-2.0.

These binaries run on the target Ingenic SoC during the bootstrap process.
They are not executed on the host computer.

================================================================================
4. DDR Configuration
================================================================================

DDR timing parameters are derived from publicly available DDR chip datasheets
(ESMT, Winbond, Samsung, etc.) and are functional hardware specifications.
The DDR binary format was determined through analysis of USB traffic to
understand the register layout required by Ingenic's DDR controller hardware.

================================================================================
5. Flash Chip Database
================================================================================

SPI NOR and NAND flash chip parameters (JEDEC IDs, timing, commands) are
derived from publicly available chip datasheets. JEDEC IDs are industry-standard
identifiers defined by JEDEC Solid State Technology Association.

